Debate&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Psychology</em>, 34(1): 1&ndash;27.
doi:10.1080/09515089.2020.1859100</li>

<li>Moore, Richard, 2013, &ldquo;Social Learning and Teaching in
Chimpanzees&rdquo;, <em>Biology &amp; Philosophy</em>, 28(6):
879&ndash;901. doi:10.1007/s10539-013-9394-y</li>

<li>Moore, Richard and Rachael L. Brown, 2022, &ldquo;Social
Inheritance and the Social Mind: Introduction to the Synthese Topical
Collection <em>The Cultural Evolution of Human Social
Cognition</em>&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 200(3): article 225.
doi:10.1007/s11229-022-03496-2</li>

<li>Nanay, Bence, 2020, &ldquo;Vicarious Representation: A New Theory
of Social Cognition&rdquo;, <em>Cognition</em>, 205: 104451.
doi:10.1016/j.cognition.2020.104451</li>

<li>Nawroth, Christian, Jan Langbein, Marjorie Coulon, Vivian Gabor,
Susann Oesterwind, Judith Benz-Schwarzburg, and Eberhard Von Borell,
2019, &ldquo;Farm Animal Cognition&mdash;Linking Behavior, Welfare and
